(secondQuint)Study of Perampanel as Adjunctive Treatment for Inadequately Controlled Seizures Associated With Lennox-Gastaut Syndrome.

 This is a multicenter, double-blind, randomized, placebo-controlled, parallel-group study of perampanel as adjunctive therapy in participants with inadequately controlled seizures associated with LGS.

 The study will consist of 3 phases: Prerandomization (4 to 8 weeks), Randomization (22 weeks), and Extension (56 weeks).

